OL,5, The number of pupils absent from state 
OL,6, schools in England rose by two-thirds  
OL,7, (67%) to 204,000 over the two weeks to 
OL,8, Thursday, 30 September.                
OL,10,FA Department for Education survey shows
OL,11,F2.5% of pupils were out of school for  
OL,12,FCovid-related reasons on this day.     
OL,14,FOverall, attendance was 89.5% in all   
OL,15,Fstate schools - meaning 10.5% of pupils
OL,16,Fwere absent, for Covid-related and     
OL,17,Fother reasons.                         
OL,19,FIn secondary schools, one in seven     
OL,20,F(13.7%) pupils was out of school.      
